This paper deals with game theory and voting systems, which are typically categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) in arXiv. The paper also discusses the concept of fairness and efficiency in voting systems, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of coalitions and subsets, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the application of simple games in real-world scenarios, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
